            <dateline>Queen’s Coll., Oxford. Aug. 18 / 1913.</dateline>
            <opener>Dear Sir, </opener>
            <p>Many thanks for your instructive article on the Meroitic<note n="1" place="foot" type="editorial">
                  <bibl>
                     <ref target="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.bibliography#BIBL.71">Schuchardt, Hugo. 1913. 'Das Meroitische'. In Wiener Zeitschrift für die Kunde des Morgenlandes (27): 163–183.</ref>
                  </bibl>
               </note>. Your conclusion agrees with the archeological evidence: the sculptures before the Negro period represent the Meroites as of an Abyssinian (not Nubian) type, with thin lips, Greek noses &amp; high pre=heads. They were non darkskinned.</p>
            <closer>
               <salute>Believe me to be </salute>
               <lb/>
               <salute>Yours faithfully</salute>
               <lb/>
               <signed>
                  <persName ref="[authorityLink]">A. H. Sayce.</persName>
               </signed>
            </closer>
         </div>
